(42, 9, 25, 61, 2, 15, 17, 'lose himself, or be cast away', 'Loss of Self and Unrighteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of pursuing worldly gain at the expense of one''s integrity. Luke warns against losing oneself for material advantage, while 2 Peter critiques those who forsake righteousness for profit, illustrating a similar theme of spiritual loss.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
